      "comment": "HAPPY AND NUMB (3) was well fancied last time on the strength of the win two back but could only manage second (22.24) at Ballarat. Top chance in this line up. PAW DROGO (2) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (22.19) at Warrnambool over 390m. Expecting another good run. GENESIS BALE (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Paw Harkonnen (23.77) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Must be included in calculations. PAW OPPA (8) should be thereabouts.",
